, Nigeria (LLB); 2002 \"},{\"col1\":\"The Nigerian Law School; 2004\"},{\"col1\":\"University of London (LL.M in International Business Law) 2018\"}]','[{\"col1\":\"Corporate and Commercial Law \"},{\"col1\":\"Legal Advisory\"},{\"col1\":\"Company Secretarial \"},{\"col1\":\"Regulatory Compliance \"},{\"col1\":\"Intellectual Property \"},{\"col1\":\"Business Start-ups \"},{\"col1\":\"International Investments \"},{\"col1\":\"Private Equity \"},{\"col1\":\"\"}]',NULL,'[{\"col1\":\"Participated with the corporate team in the winding-up of the subsidiary of a multi-national oil servicing firm and assisted in ensuring that outstanding (debts) receivables are recovered on behalf of the company.\"},{\"col1\":\"Represented African Capital Alliance, a leading African private equity company, in conducting legal due diligence and structuring a management buy-in culminating in a purchase of equities worth $15 million USD.\"},{\"col1\":\"Acted for a land drilling company in an $18 million private equity investment.\"},{\"col1\":\"Advised and assistd several clients on the establishment of Nigerian subsidiaries and procuring relevant pre-investment and operational approvals, licenses and permits.\"}]','[{\"col1\":\"\"}]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"archived\":0,\"locale\":\"en_us\",\"localeEnabled\":1,\"slug\":null,\"uri\":null,\"dateCreated\":null,\"dateUpdated\":null,\"root\":null,\"lft\":null,\"rgt\":null,\"level\":null,\"searchScore\":null,\"elementId\":0,\"metaType\":\"template\",\"metaPath\":\"\",\"seoMainEntityCategory\":\"Person\",\"seoMainEntityOfPage\":\"\",\"seoTitle\":\"Ijeoma Abalogu\",\"seoDescription\":\"Ijeoma Abalogu is a Senior Associate at GBC. Ijeoma heads the Firm\\u2019s Business Advisory and Company Secretarial unit. She has over 11 years practice experience and has advised several companies on the establishment of business entities in Nigeria, as well as completed registration and obtaining relev