d to due diligence matters.&nbsp;</p>','[{\"col1\":\"Ambrose Alli University (LLB); 2004 \"},{\"col1\":\"The Nigerian Law School; 2005\"}]','[{\"col1\":\"Corporate Commercial Litigation \"},{\"col1\":\"Corporate and Commercial Law \"},{\"col1\":\"Legal Research and Advisory\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\\u00a0\"},{\"col1\":\"Regulatory and Compliance \"},{\"col1\":\"Labour and Employment & Arbitration\"}]','[{\"col1\":\"The Nigerian Bar Association \"},{\"col1\":\"Chartered Institute of Arbitrators (UK)\"}]','[{\"col1\":\"Represented clients on various tax and regulatory disputes.\"},{\"col1\":\"Provided representation for an international professional services firm in a N1.4 billion action involving the preparation of a report by it on the issue of the incorrectly stated profit by a publicly quoted company in Nigeria.\"},{\"col1\":\"Represented a multi-national oil company with regards to issues raised by several different human rights organisations in respect of a labour matter regarding one of its employees.\"},{\"col1\":\"Advised a multinational oil service company with regards to its liabilities and responsibilities in connection with the environmental impact of the company\\u2019s drilling activities in the Niger-Delta region of Nigeria.\"},{\"col1\":\"Advised African Capital Alliance, a leading private equity firm in Nigeria in connection with the acquisition and financing of an interest in a gas processing plant involving a combination of equity and mezzanine finance and reviewing and advising on the various Gas Agreements and the EPC contract.\"},{\"col1\":\"Advised a Nigerian company involved in the provision of underwater dive activities within the Nigerian oil and gas industry on the liability for the loss of a remotely operated vehicle (ROV).\"},{\"col1\":\"Represented a multi-national oil service company in a law suit with regards to illegally imposed taxes by a local government authority. \"},{\"col1\":\"Advised African Capital Alliance, a leading private equity firm in Nigeria in connection with the acquisition of controlling interest and financing of the pre-eminent cash-in-transit operator in Nigeria.\"},{\"col1\":\"Advised African Capital Alliance, a leading private equity firm in Nigeria in connection with the merger of two of the biggest insurance providers in Nigeria.\"},{\"col1\":\"Represented a franchisor in a suit with regard to the breach of the terms of a franchise agreement by a franchisee.\"}]','[{\"col1\":\"\"}]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"archived\":0,\"locale\":\"en_us\",\"localeEnabled\":1,\"slug\":null,\"uri\":null,\"dateCreated\":null,\"dateUpdated\":null,\"root\":null,\"lft\":null,\"rgt\":null,\"level\":null,\"searchScore\":null,\"elementId\":0,\"metaType\":\"template\",\"metaPath\":\"\",\"seoMainEntityCategory\":\"Person\",\"seoMainEntityOfPage\":\"\",\"seoTitle\":\"Ayoade Oluwasanmi\",\"seoDescription\":\"Ayoade Oluwasanmi is a Senior Associate at GBC. Ayoade\\u2019s main area of interest is Commercial Litigation and he is a member of the litigation group at Gbenga Biobaku & Co. Ayoade is an astute litigator with over 10 years \\u2018hands on\\u2019 experience and has represented clients in proceedings at various Courts in Nigeria including appeals at the Court of Appeal.\",\"seoKeywords\":\"gbenga biobaku & co, gbc, law, nigeria, Ayoade, Oluwasanmi, commercial litigation, Chartered Institute of Arbitrators\",\"seoImageTransform\":\"\",\"seoFacebookImageTransform\":\"\",\"seoTwitterImageTransform\":\"\",\"twitterCardType\":\"summary\",\"openGraphType\":\"website\",\"robots\":\"\",\"seoImageId\":\"65\",\"seoTwitterImageId\":\"65\",\"seoFacebookImageId\":\"65\",\"seoTitleUnparsed\":\"Ayoade Oluwasanmi\",\"seoDescriptionUnparsed\":\"Ayoade Oluwasanmi is a Senior Associate at GBC. Ayoade\\u2019s main area of interest is Commercial Litigation and he is a member of the litigation group at Gbenga Biobaku & Co. Ayoade is an astute litigator with 