nbsp;and arbitral proceedings arising from various commercial transactions spanning oil and gas, banking and finance, taxation, investment disputes, employment, and real estate. Ayoade regularly appears for clients in various courts across Nigeria, including at the Court of Appeal, and&nbsp;before regulatory agencies and other governmental bodies. He has represented the firm’s clients at several parliamentary investigations and hearings before the Nigerian National Assembly, and also provides support to GBC\'s Corporate and Commercial team on legal due diligence assignments.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> Ayoade holds a Bachelor of Laws degree from Ambrose Alli University, is a Legal Practitioner of the Supreme Court of Nigeria, and is a member of the Chartered Institute of Arbitrators UK (Nigeria Branch).</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> He loves playing chess, reading novels, and has an avid interest in football. Ayoade also takes a keen interest in current affairs as evidenced by his participation in 2009 in the TV current affairs game show: “Who Wants to be a Millionaire”, in which he made it to the “hot seat” and won N2million.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> We are confident Ayoade’s appointment as a Partner further enriches our litigation team and&nbsp;greatly strengthens GBC for now and into the future.</p><hr><p>Gbenga Biobaku</p><p>Senior Partner</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Gbenga Biobaku & Co.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> 11 Babafemi Osoba Crescent</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Off Admiralty Road, Lekki Phase 1</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Lagos, Nigeria</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Telephone:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 234 1 2717769</p>\r\n\r\n<p> D/L:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 234 1 2706382</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Mobile:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 234 (0) 08036410000</p><p><br></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Gbenga Biobaku & Co. (GBC) is pleased to announce the promotion o